WEBVTT

00:08.107 --> 00:14.179
♪♪

00:14.181 --> 00:20.519
♪♪

00:20.521 --> 00:22.921
Elderly Woman:
So, you're writing a book?

00:22.923 --> 00:26.258
I didn't know
they still wrote books.

00:26.260 --> 00:28.127
Author:
Willard's Mill. Yes.

00:28.129 --> 00:33.599
The witch burnings
and the supposed curse.

00:33.601 --> 00:35.334
[Chuckles]

00:35.336 --> 00:38.670
Yes, "supposed."

00:38.672 --> 00:39.838
And you were the...?

00:39.840 --> 00:41.740
Sheriff.
Sheriff.

00:41.742 --> 00:45.811
Sheriff of Willard's Mill
for a long, long time. Hm.

00:45.813 --> 00:48.214
Could you state
your name?
[Beeps]

00:48.216 --> 00:50.816
Uh, my name is...

00:50.818 --> 00:54.219
Evelyn Barret.

00:54.221 --> 00:55.520
Can you tell me about

00:55.522 --> 00:59.958
the Sheriff who preceded you,
Stan Miller?

00:59.960 --> 01:02.694
Stan...

01:02.696 --> 01:04.763
Stan was...

01:04.765 --> 01:06.565
a very good man.

01:06.567 --> 01:07.766
♪♪

01:07.768 --> 01:11.036
Don't get me wrong --
he could drive you crazy,

01:11.038 --> 01:15.240
but I trusted him
with my life.

01:15.242 --> 01:17.443
♪♪

01:17.445 --> 01:20.378
And then, Stan changed....

01:20.380 --> 01:22.114
♪♪

01:22.116 --> 01:25.651
...into
something different.

01:25.653 --> 01:28.954
What do you mean,
someone different?

01:28.956 --> 01:32.324
I didn't say someone --

01:32.326 --> 01:34.927
I said<i> something.</i>

01:34.929 --> 01:36.862
[Insects chirping]

01:36.864 --> 01:43.535
♪♪

01:43.537 --> 01:52.077
♪♪

01:52.079 --> 01:54.547
[Roaring]

01:54.549 --> 01:58.149
♪♪

01:58.151 --> 02:00.419
[Rumbling]

02:00.421 --> 02:08.894
♪♪

02:08.896 --> 02:11.764
No! No, please!

02:11.766 --> 02:16.235
Lord Haurus, please!

02:16.237 --> 02:18.003
Please!

02:18.005 --> 02:22.308
♪♪

02:22.310 --> 02:26.378
Aah!
Let me join you!

02:26.380 --> 02:28.380
Please!

02:28.382 --> 02:30.916
No, Lord Haurus!

02:30.918 --> 02:32.717
Please!

02:32.719 --> 02:34.720
[Screams]

02:34.722 --> 02:36.788
♪♪

02:36.790 --> 02:40.592
[Screaming]

02:40.594 --> 02:42.728
[Cawing, screaming]

02:42.730 --> 02:45.530
♪♪

02:45.532 --> 02:48.267
[Screams]

02:48.269 --> 02:49.835
[Roars]

02:49.837 --> 02:52.271
[Screams]

02:52.273 --> 02:58.010
♪♪

02:58.012 --> 03:06.085
♪♪

03:06.087 --> 03:14.293
♪♪

03:14.295 --> 03:22.233
♪♪

03:22.235 --> 03:28.707
And this is what I found
this morning.

03:28.709 --> 03:38.517
♪♪

03:38.519 --> 03:40.986
Huh.

03:40.988 --> 03:43.722
Hachi machi.

03:43.724 --> 03:52.197
♪♪

03:52.199 --> 03:54.934
I think it's really him.

03:54.936 --> 03:56.936
Oh, my God.

03:56.938 --> 03:58.937
It's over?

03:58.939 --> 03:59.871
♪♪

03:59.873 --> 04:03.275
Is this --
Is this all over?

04:03.277 --> 04:07.012
And you didn't see anything?
How is that possible?

04:07.014 --> 04:09.681
Because I don't live
at the cemetery.

04:09.683 --> 04:11.483
I know everybody thinks
I'm this weirdo,

04:11.485 --> 04:13.552
but I'm just a guy
with a job.

04:13.554 --> 04:15.720
Sorry. Sorry.

04:15.722 --> 04:18.557
Actually, where were you
last night, just for the record?

04:18.559 --> 04:20.759
I was on the roof of
the abandoned shopping mall.

04:22.363 --> 04:26.498
Sheriff,
have you ever seen a UFO?

04:26.500 --> 04:28.833
I mean, a real one?

04:28.835 --> 04:30.102
They only land
if you're nude.

04:30.104 --> 04:32.104
Oh, my for God's sake.
You know what? Could you --

04:32.106 --> 04:34.172
Could I just -- Can I --
Please?

04:34.174 --> 04:35.307
Mm-hmm.

04:37.110 --> 04:38.844
Don't learn.

04:38.846 --> 04:44.449
♪♪

04:44.451 --> 04:50.055
♪♪

04:50.057 --> 04:52.658
[Door opens, closes]
Evie: Stan!

04:52.660 --> 04:54.259
Stan!

04:54.261 --> 04:55.660
Stan!

04:55.662 --> 04:57.730
I am glad
you are sitting down.

04:59.867 --> 05:02.067
Is everything okay?

05:02.069 --> 05:03.535
Couldn't be better.

05:05.472 --> 05:08.940
Great. Okay.
Are you ready?

05:08.942 --> 05:11.810
Constable. Eccles.

05:11.812 --> 05:14.880
Is. Dead.

05:14.882 --> 05:18.283
[Laughs]

05:18.285 --> 05:19.351
Dynamite.

05:19.353 --> 05:21.820
Oh, I'm not kidding.
I'm not kidding.

05:21.822 --> 05:23.622
I-I-It's definitely him.

05:23.624 --> 05:25.423
He was burned at the stake
at the old cemetery.

05:25.425 --> 05:29.027
Everything.
And all the graves are empty.

05:29.029 --> 05:30.295
♪♪

05:30.297 --> 05:32.231
I guess
we're in the clear, then.

05:32.233 --> 05:34.332
♪♪

05:34.334 --> 05:35.968
Wow. To -- To --
To be honest,

05:35.970 --> 05:39.371
I guess I was expecting
kind of a bigger reaction.

05:39.373 --> 05:42.641
I mean, I've seen you get
more excited over women's golf.

05:42.643 --> 05:45.644
♪♪

05:45.646 --> 05:47.245
[Breathes deeply]

05:47.247 --> 05:49.915
Okay. Uh...

05:49.917 --> 05:51.917
Well, I-I guess I just thought
you'd want to know

05:51.919 --> 05:54.385
that we are...

05:54.387 --> 05:56.321
free of the death curse

05:56.323 --> 05:58.990
and that our lives just got
[Chuckling] a whole lot easier.

05:58.992 --> 06:01.593
[Knuckles cracking]

06:01.595 --> 06:02.861
♪♪

06:02.863 --> 06:05.564
[Groans softly]

06:05.566 --> 06:08.066
But, uh...

06:08.068 --> 06:09.467
I guess I'll -- I'll...

06:09.469 --> 06:11.536
I'll just see you around.

06:11.538 --> 06:17.576
♪♪

06:17.578 --> 06:19.277
I'm not doing it.

06:19.279 --> 06:21.212
[Door opens, closes]

06:21.214 --> 06:27.485
♪♪

06:27.487 --> 06:30.022
[Cheerful music plays]
[Man whistling]

06:30.024 --> 06:39.164
♪♪

06:39.166 --> 06:48.173
♪♪

06:48.175 --> 06:57.315
♪♪

06:57.317 --> 07:06.325
♪♪

07:06.327 --> 07:15.401
♪♪

07:15.403 --> 07:17.068
[Music ends]

07:17.070 --> 07:25.977
♪♪

07:25.979 --> 07:27.413
[Scoffs]

07:27.415 --> 07:28.547
Stan?

07:28.549 --> 07:30.815
What are you doing?

07:30.817 --> 07:33.351
I don't know.

07:33.353 --> 07:34.519
[Door creaks]

07:34.521 --> 07:36.688
Aaaand there you go.

07:36.690 --> 07:38.757
I made it home
without a lick of help.

07:38.759 --> 07:40.459
And I knew you would.

07:40.461 --> 07:43.962
That's why I followed you,
to prove it.

07:43.964 --> 07:48.834
♪♪

07:48.836 --> 07:50.835
So...

07:50.837 --> 07:52.905
good job!

07:52.907 --> 07:59.444
♪♪

07:59.446 --> 08:00.445
[Groans softly]

08:00.447 --> 08:04.182
Haurus:
Your willpower is fading.

08:04.184 --> 08:06.051
You can feel it.

08:06.053 --> 08:09.654
We'll only get closer
and closer...

08:09.656 --> 08:12.390
and then
it will be done.

08:12.392 --> 08:14.792
Is that right?

08:14.794 --> 08:17.596
You think I'm gonna
kill Evie Barret?

08:17.598 --> 08:22.233
You knew killing Eccles
came with a price.

08:22.235 --> 08:24.936
Dad! Guess what --

08:24.938 --> 08:27.939
Kevin has that whole section
of the old cemetery open now,

08:27.941 --> 08:29.741
and I am going to
convince him

08:29.743 --> 08:31.810
to put in
a miniature-golf course.

08:31.812 --> 08:34.412
You're not even listening to me.
I don't even care.

08:34.414 --> 08:37.015
I've said my piece,
and now I'm leaving.

08:37.017 --> 08:38.951
Whoo! [Chuckles]

08:38.953 --> 08:41.353
♪♪

08:41.355 --> 08:43.087
Why don't you kill me?

08:43.089 --> 08:44.422
♪♪

08:44.424 --> 08:46.892
If I make someone a king

08:46.894 --> 08:49.694
and they bring me
the head of a peasant,

08:49.696 --> 08:52.230
should I be satisfied?

08:52.232 --> 08:55.099
The peasant means nothing.

08:55.101 --> 08:59.370
But if the king brings me
the head of his brother,

08:59.372 --> 09:02.641
then his soul
is destroyed,

09:02.643 --> 09:06.311
and I am appeased.

09:06.313 --> 09:08.246
Why's it got to be a king
and a peasant?

09:08.248 --> 09:11.716
Why -- Why can't it be a plumber
and his pal Steve?

09:11.718 --> 09:15.320
Why does everything got to be
so goddamn fruity?

09:15.322 --> 09:16.587
Huh?

09:16.589 --> 09:17.722
♪♪

09:17.724 --> 09:19.190
Who's Steve?

09:19.192 --> 09:23.928
♪♪

09:23.930 --> 09:25.797
[Television turns on]

09:25.799 --> 09:27.399
[Sighs]

09:27.401 --> 09:29.067
<i> [Golf club swings]</i>

09:29.069 --> 09:30.402
<i> [Applause]</i>

09:30.404 --> 09:32.003
Announcer:
<i> You're watching women's golf</i>

09:32.005 --> 09:35.807
<i> on the Women's Golf Channel,</i>
<i> your home for women's golf.</i>

09:35.809 --> 09:38.343
<i> We'll be back</i>
<i> with more women's golf</i>

09:38.345 --> 09:40.946
<i> after this important word</i>
<i> about women's golf.</i>

09:40.948 --> 09:44.749
<i> That reminds me of a funny</i>
<i> story about women's golf,</i>

09:44.751 --> 09:46.952
<i> not that there's anything funny</i>
<i> about women's golf.</i>

09:51.057 --> 09:55.360
♪♪

09:55.362 --> 09:57.896
Evie!
Yeah?

09:57.898 --> 10:00.966
So much for Willard's Mill
staying quiet.
What happened?

10:00.968 --> 10:03.035
There's an ethnic gang fight
at the laundromat.

10:03.037 --> 10:04.836
Leon, you can't say that.

10:04.838 --> 10:07.573
It's a bunch of Dutch ladies
handing out butter cookies.

10:07.575 --> 10:09.440
You tell me
what to call it.

10:09.442 --> 10:10.642
You know what?

10:10.644 --> 10:13.244
Why don't you knock off early
and go fold those whites?

10:13.246 --> 10:16.048
I don't see whites --
just laundry.

10:31.665 --> 10:37.936
♪♪

10:40.240 --> 10:41.707
[Engine starts]

10:46.179 --> 10:48.413
[Seat belt clicks]

10:48.415 --> 10:50.915
[Roars]
[Gasping]

10:50.917 --> 10:53.485
♪♪

10:53.487 --> 10:56.788
[Breathing heavily]

11:01.161 --> 11:08.500
♪♪

11:08.502 --> 11:15.507
♪♪

11:15.509 --> 11:17.776
Duquette:
If you're looking for a way out,

11:17.778 --> 11:19.645
you can stop looking.

11:19.647 --> 11:23.514
♪♪

11:23.516 --> 11:25.249
You tricked me.

11:25.251 --> 11:27.518
You lied to me.

11:27.520 --> 11:30.321
You think I ever -- ever
would have agreed to this

11:30.323 --> 11:32.858
if I knew it meant
I had to kill Evie Barret?

11:32.860 --> 11:34.926
♪♪

11:34.928 --> 11:37.195
Have you ever heard
of a deal with the devil

11:37.197 --> 11:39.931
that worked out great?

11:39.933 --> 11:42.533
I said, and I quote,

11:42.535 --> 11:45.603
"Hell is for the alone
and unconnected,"

11:45.605 --> 11:49.908
and then you agreed
to become a part of it.

11:49.910 --> 11:53.745
So everyone I love,
everyone I'm connected to...

11:53.747 --> 11:57.215
Gets destroyed by you.

11:57.217 --> 11:59.384
Haurus did that...

11:59.386 --> 12:01.820
like that.
[Snaps fingers]

12:01.822 --> 12:04.956
And now you're
a part of him.

12:04.958 --> 12:06.891
And that doesn't work

12:06.893 --> 12:12.030
if your soul is brimming
with love and happiness.

12:12.032 --> 12:14.699
Of course not.

12:14.701 --> 12:16.034
Of course not.

12:16.036 --> 12:17.703
♪♪

12:17.705 --> 12:20.038
'Cause that's
everything he isn't.

12:20.040 --> 12:23.441
♪♪

12:23.443 --> 12:24.976
And that'd kill him.

12:24.978 --> 12:26.511
♪♪

12:26.513 --> 12:28.313
That would kill him.
[Whoosh]

12:28.315 --> 12:34.385
♪♪

12:34.387 --> 12:36.154
[Shovel scraping]
Denise:
Just think about it, Kevin.

12:36.156 --> 12:37.856
You go and you visit
your loved ones,

12:37.858 --> 12:39.457
and then -- boom! --
[chuckles]

12:39.459 --> 12:40.791
you can play mini-golf.

12:40.793 --> 12:42.060
[Chuckles]

12:42.062 --> 12:44.195
Hey! No!

12:44.197 --> 12:45.797
Hey, kids.

12:45.799 --> 12:48.399
You dig up this woman
every week!

12:48.401 --> 12:49.968
This is the last time,
I promise.

12:57.544 --> 12:59.177
I'm sorry, dear.

13:02.416 --> 13:04.649
[Smooches]

13:04.651 --> 13:06.818
All right.

13:06.820 --> 13:08.019
[Grunts]

13:10.423 --> 13:13.758
Hey, Kev-o, you, uh...

13:13.760 --> 13:16.528
you're my best friend,
right?

13:16.530 --> 13:17.428
Yeah?

13:17.430 --> 13:19.697
Can I ask you
a personal question?

13:19.699 --> 13:20.698
Yeah.

13:20.700 --> 13:22.033
What's your last name?

13:23.703 --> 13:25.703
Cougar-Mellencamp.

13:25.705 --> 13:27.205
No relation.

13:27.207 --> 13:28.607
Good enough.

13:28.609 --> 13:29.974
Hey, Kev-o...

13:29.976 --> 13:31.609
look after her.

13:31.611 --> 13:33.177
Or you look after him.

13:33.179 --> 13:34.512
I don't know
which one is worse.

13:34.514 --> 13:36.647
So, I'll tell you what
you should look into

13:36.649 --> 13:38.449
is an assisted-care
facility --

13:38.451 --> 13:40.085
let them do
the heavy lifting.

13:41.454 --> 13:43.188
Sweetheart.

13:43.190 --> 13:44.723
Kev-o.

13:52.399 --> 13:54.399
That's my mom.

13:58.138 --> 14:03.574
♪♪

14:03.576 --> 14:08.947
♪♪

14:08.949 --> 14:11.482
[Telephone rings]

14:11.484 --> 14:12.951
What?
Evie:<i> Please, Stan!</i>

14:12.953 --> 14:14.419
<i> It's an emergency!</i>
<i> I'm at my house!</i>

14:14.421 --> 14:16.154
What?
<i> You have to help me!</i>

14:16.156 --> 14:17.555
<i> [Clicks]</i>

14:17.557 --> 14:23.695
♪♪

14:23.697 --> 14:25.363
Evie?

14:25.365 --> 14:26.431
Don't move.

14:26.433 --> 14:28.399
[Sighs]

14:28.401 --> 14:29.634
♪♪

14:32.738 --> 14:34.172
Get down there
by the fireplace!

14:34.174 --> 14:36.507
Come on.
Stan!

14:36.509 --> 14:38.243
Evie, you don't want
to do this.
Keep walking.

14:38.245 --> 14:40.711
Believe me, you d--
Keep walking!

14:40.713 --> 14:42.180
♪♪

14:42.182 --> 14:44.315
Sit down.

14:44.317 --> 14:46.217
Cuff yourself to the grate.
Oh, come on.

14:46.219 --> 14:48.019
Cuff yourself to the grate.

14:48.021 --> 14:50.121
It's anchored to the floor.

14:50.123 --> 14:54.459
♪♪

14:54.461 --> 14:55.726
Don't try anything.

14:55.728 --> 14:57.328
[Sizzles]
[Groaning]

14:57.330 --> 14:59.730
Okay, I -- I did have a fire
in there earlier.

14:59.732 --> 15:01.199
I wasn't pla-- It's --
I'm sorry.

15:01.201 --> 15:03.201
So just try not to brush up
against it.

15:03.203 --> 15:04.502
♪♪

15:04.504 --> 15:06.271
Look, I don't like this
any more than you do,

15:06.273 --> 15:08.473
but I need answers.

15:08.475 --> 15:11.142
I -- I thought
we were in the clear, Stan.

15:11.144 --> 15:13.811
I mean, Eccles was dead.

15:13.813 --> 15:16.181
Then, earlier today,
that thing --

15:16.183 --> 15:19.617
that "Judy" thing --

15:19.619 --> 15:21.219
tried to kill me,

15:21.221 --> 15:23.621
and I think
you can tell me why.

15:23.623 --> 15:24.955
♪♪

15:24.957 --> 15:26.757
Why do you think that?

15:26.759 --> 15:29.226
Because
I ran the fingerprints

15:29.228 --> 15:31.228
it left
on my windshield...

15:31.230 --> 15:32.964
♪♪

15:32.966 --> 15:34.566
...and they were yours.

15:34.568 --> 15:40.938
♪♪

15:40.940 --> 15:43.174
Judy's real name
is "Haurus."

15:43.176 --> 15:45.977
Haurus...helped me
to kill Eccles,

15:45.979 --> 15:47.312
and now Haurus...

15:47.314 --> 15:52.884
♪♪

15:52.886 --> 15:54.252
Haurus wants me
to kill you.

15:54.254 --> 15:55.720
Oh, Stan.
I can't believe --

15:55.722 --> 15:57.789
I don't know how much longer
I can hold Haurus off.

15:57.791 --> 15:59.357
[Sizzles]
Ow! Son of a...

15:59.359 --> 16:01.025
Sorry! I said don't brush up
against it.

16:01.027 --> 16:04.195
Would you please
get me some ice?
Yes. All right.

16:04.197 --> 16:07.065
Would you please
just get me some ice!
I -- All right! I am --

16:07.067 --> 16:12.103
♪♪

16:12.105 --> 16:14.338
You know, Stan,
you should've just told me.

16:14.340 --> 16:16.975
I mean,
we can figure this out.

16:19.011 --> 16:21.546
[Screams]
[Roars]

16:21.548 --> 16:24.148
Stan: No!

16:24.150 --> 16:26.351
[Clattering]

16:26.353 --> 16:29.054
Son of a bitch.

16:30.724 --> 16:32.157
[Exhales sharply]

16:32.159 --> 16:35.292
♪♪

16:35.294 --> 16:36.994
[Sighs]

16:36.996 --> 16:45.236
♪♪

16:45.238 --> 16:53.310
♪♪

16:53.312 --> 17:01.519
♪♪

17:01.521 --> 17:08.726
♪♪

17:08.728 --> 17:09.927
[Sighs]

17:09.929 --> 17:11.796
[Telephone rings]

17:11.798 --> 17:13.198
Hello?!

17:13.200 --> 17:14.599
♪♪

17:14.601 --> 17:15.666
Yes.

17:15.668 --> 17:17.468
♪♪

17:17.470 --> 17:18.870
[Receiver clicks]

17:18.872 --> 17:24.542
♪♪

17:24.544 --> 17:26.410
[Panting]

17:26.412 --> 17:28.546
♪♪

17:28.548 --> 17:32.283
Evie,
you know what they say --

17:32.285 --> 17:35.953
good can't defeat evil

17:35.955 --> 17:38.956
and that, if you want
to defeat evil,

17:38.958 --> 17:42.293
you got to go out
and find a bigger evil...

17:42.295 --> 17:44.295
and let a little in.

17:44.297 --> 17:47.432
Not sure I believe that,
but, okay.

17:47.434 --> 17:51.436
Only way we defeated Hitler was
by making a pact with Stalin.

17:51.438 --> 17:52.970
♪♪

17:52.972 --> 17:56.374
Just I'm clear,
am I Hitler or Stalin in this?

17:56.376 --> 17:59.577
Look, the only reason
you're here to begin with...

17:59.579 --> 18:01.245
♪♪

18:01.247 --> 18:03.648
...is 'cause I beat the hell out
of a witch at a funeral

18:03.650 --> 18:05.784
and got fired.

18:05.786 --> 18:08.620
None of this
was meant for you.

18:08.622 --> 18:10.454
It was all meant for me.

18:10.456 --> 18:11.722
♪♪

18:11.724 --> 18:13.525
And I'm so sorry.

18:13.527 --> 18:14.925
♪♪

18:14.927 --> 18:17.796
But he's comin'...

18:17.798 --> 18:20.331
and I can't fight him
no more.

18:20.333 --> 18:23.467
♪♪

